[5
Source: ALEXANDER MOHAMED Associated Press Writer
MOGADISHU, Somalia (AP)

Reports reaching Mogadishu say outbreaks of measles and cholera are
occurring in most of southern Somalia, including the Indian Ocean port
of Kismayo, 300 miles south of Mogadishu. Dr. Faysal Abdulkadir said 70
people
have been diagnosed with cholera and have been quarantined.
