[7
Date: Sun, 24 Jan 1999
From: Chan Yow Cheong <chanyowcheong@pacific.net.sg>
ProMED-mail Regional Moderator for Asia
Source: The Independent (Dhaka, Bangladesh), 24 Jan 1999 [edited

DIARRHOEA CLAIMS 30 LIVES IN FARIDPUR (BANGLADESH)
Diarrhoea that has broken out in an epidemic form in three thanas
[sub-districts of the district [of Faridpur has claimed 30 lives so
far, according to unofficial sources. Besides, about 5,000 people have
been attacked with diarrhoea which is still spreading fast in the areas.
The thanas affected with diarrhoea are Nagarkanda, Sadarpur and Bhanga.
When contacted, the Civil Surgeon of Faridpur admitted the outbreak of
diarrhoea in an epidemic form in the aforesaid areas but he said that
there was no official report of death. However, the Civil Surgeon
informed that several medical teams have been formed and sent to the
affected areas to combat the disease.
